docs.summary: Triggered when a file is deleted, the move_to_trash flag indicates if the delete was permanent or a move to trash operation
Triggered when essential post upload processing failed
Triggered when a file is ready to be consumed including any post upload processing
Triggered when a file is updated (for example, name change, labels change or the file is moved).
Triggered when a folder is created. the triggered_by_undelete flag indicates if the create was caused by a restore from trash operation
Triggered when a folder is deleted, the move_to_trash flag indicates if the delete was permanent or a move to trash operation
Triggered when a folder is updated (name change or move).
